'''Kanno Shrine''' (かんのじんじゃ) is a historic shrine in Kanno, {{ill|lt=Manno|Q1350204|qid=Q1350204|1=Mannō, Kagawa}}, {{ill|lt=Nakatado District|Q1206155|qid=Q1206155|1=Nakatado District, Kagawa}}, {{ill|lt=Kagawa Prefecture|Q161454|qid=Q161454|1=Kagawa Prefecture}}. It was enshrined as guardian deity of {{ill|lt=Mannō Pond|Q20983084|qid=Q20983084|1=Manno Lake}} and counted as one of the 24 Engishiki shrines of Sanuki.

The enshrined deities are said to be {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Mizuhanome no Mikoto|1=UNKNOWN}}, {{ill|UNKNOWN|qid=Q10940685|lt=Ame-no-Hohi no Mikoto|1=Ame no Hohi}}, {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Wakeikazuchi no Mikoto|1=UNKNOWN}}, and {{ill|lt=Emperor Sujun|Q316654|qid=Q316654|1=Emperor Saga}}<ref>[http://kagawa.bine.jp/jinnjya/manou/53kano/kanno53.html Kanno Shrine]</ref>.
